  "editorial": {
    "headline": "Reynolds' Two Homers Fuel Pittsburgh Comeback Win",
    "subheadline": "Pittsburgh Pirates rallies past Oakland Athletics, PIT 6, ATH 5.",
    "lead_angle": "Bryan Reynolds' relentless bat led the Pittsburgh Pirates to a 6-5 victory over the Oakland Athletics, completing a four-run comeback. Reynolds blasted his second home run of the game, a two-run shot in the seventh inning that tied the contest, setting the stage for Pittsburgh's decisive ninth-inning run off losing pitcher Elvis Alvarado. Mason Montgomery earned the win in relief, with Gregory Soto notching the save.\n\nThe Oakland Athletics sprinted to an early four-run lead in the first inning. Pittsburgh began chipping away with a solo homer from Brandon Lowe in the fourth. The game turned dramatically in the seventh after Zack Gelof had put Oakland ahead 5-3 with a solo blast in the sixth. Undeterred, the Pirates rallied. Reynolds then launched his second home run of the game, a two-run shot, leveling the score at five runs apiece against Oakland pitching.\n\nReynolds was the undisputed catalyst for the Pittsburgh Pirates, finishing the day 4-for-5 with two home runs and three runs batted in. His persistent hitting kept the Pirates within reach, ultimately setting the stage for their ninth-inning triumph. This critical road victory strengthens Pittsburgh’s pursuit of a postseason berth, while the Oakland Athletics find their own playoff aspirations dimmed by the narrow, hard-fought loss.",
    "reason": "A 4-run comeback is the day's best storyline — resilience over résumé."
